        <div class="faq-section-head">
          <span class="faq-section-icon" aria-hidden="true"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="M2 3h6a4 4 0 0 1 4 4v14a3 3 0 0 0-3-3H2z"/><path d="M22 3h-6a4 4 0 0 0-4 4v14a3 3 0 0 1 3-3h7z"/></svg></span>
          <h2>Student FAQs</h2>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-list">
        <details class="faq-item">
          <summary>What is Career-Infrastructure-as-a-Service (CIaaS)?</summary>
          <div class="faq-answer">
            <p>BridgeDegree is Nigeria's first CIaaS platform, the missing operating system between a Nigerian university and the global economy. We provide a structured, verifiable, longitudinal programme that converts academic years into career leverage, from 100 Level through post-graduation.</p>
          </div>
        </details>
        <details class="faq-item">
          <summary>When do I start?</summary>
          <div class="faq-answer">
            <p>We begin at the 100 Level (Foundation tier). Value compounds each year: a student who joins at 100 Level exits with programme years of structured capital-building; joining at the 400 Level still gets Launch benefits but without the same compounding effect.</p>
          </div>
        </details>
        <details class="faq-item">
          <summary>Which universities currently partner with BridgeDegree?</summary>
          <div class="faq-answer">
            <p>We are actively onboarding partner universities across Nigeria. Reach out to bring BridgeDegree to your institution — we work with university management to embed the platform into the academic structure.</p>
          </div>
        </details>
        <details class="faq-item">
          <summary>Does this replace my SIWES or IT placement?</summary>
          <div class="faq-answer">
            <p>No. BridgeDegree complements your existing SIWES or Industrial Training placement. Our Experience Engine structures additional, longer-term verified work experience alongside your university requirements — giving you more depth and documentation than a standard placement alone.</p>
          </div>
        </details>
        <details class="faq-item">
          <summary>Will my final-year project definitely get published?</summary>
          <div class="faq-answer">
            <p>Our Publication Pipeline works to make your research publication-ready and submits it to the appropriate journals. While no one can guarantee acceptance, we provide editing support, supervision guidance, and journal matching to give your work the strongest possible chance. Many students graduate with accepted or publication-ready papers.</p>
          </div>
        </details>
        <details class="faq-item">
          <summary>Is BridgeDegree available for all courses of study?</summary>
          <div class="faq-answer">
            <p>Yes. Whether you study Engineering, Law, Medicine, Business, Sciences, Social Sciences, or Arts, BridgeDegree has pathways for your field. Placements, journal targets, and global mobility strategies are all tailored to your specific course.</p>
          </div>
        </details>
        <details class="faq-item">
          <summary>Is my data secure with BridgeDegree?</summary>
          <div class="faq-answer">
            <p>Yes. We take student data privacy seriously. All data is handled in compliance with applicable data protection regulations. See our Privacy Policy for full details on how your personal information is stored and used.</p>
          </div>
        </details>
        <details class="faq-item">
          <summary>Which universities can participate in BridgeDegree?</summary>
          <div class="faq-answer">
            <p>BridgeDegree is designed to work across all Nigerian universities and tertiary institutions. The platform is institution-neutral, meaning students from any accredited university or polytechnic can participate.</p>
          </div>
        </details>
        <details class="faq-item">
          <summary>What role do mentors play in the programme?</summary>
          <div class="faq-answer">
            <p>Every BridgeDegree student is matched with a programme mentor. Mentors provide guidance on:</p>
            <ul>
              <li>Career direction</li>
              <li>Internship preparation</li>
              <li>Professional development</li>
              <li>Research and project work</li>
              <li>Global career strategy</li>
            </ul>
            <p>Mentorship ensures students are guided throughout their academic journey.</p>
          </div>
        </details>
        <details class="faq-item">
          <summary>What is a Career Passport?</summary>
          <div class="faq-answer">
            <p>Your Career Passport is your verified professional profile inside BridgeDegree. It records:</p>
            <ul>
              <li>Internships and work experience</li>
              <li>Industry projects</li>
              <li>Certifications and skills</li>
              <li>Research publications</li>
              <li>Mentor validations</li>
              <li>Career achievements</li>
            </ul>
            <p>Unlike a CV, a Career Passport is verifiable and continuously updated throughout your journey.</p>
          </div>
        </details>
        <details class="faq-item">
          <summary>How does BridgeDegree help me get work experience?</summary>
          <div class="faq-answer">
            <p>Starting from 200 Level, BridgeDegree connects students with structured opportunities such as:</p>
            <ul>
              <li>Virtual internships</li>
              <li>Corporate project briefs</li>
              <li>Remote international work projects</li>
              <li>Industry-aligned final year projects</li>
            </ul>
            <p>All work experience is documented and verified, ensuring graduates leave university with real professional history.</p>
          </div>
        </details>
        <details class="faq-item">
          <summary>Does BridgeDegree guarantee a job?</summary>
          <div class="faq-answer">
            <p>BridgeDegree does not promise jobs. What we provide is career infrastructure that dramatically increases your employability by helping you build:</p>
            <ul>
              <li>Verifiable work experience</li>
              <li>Professional networks</li>
              <li>Industry-relevant skills</li>
              <li>A strong career portfolio</li>
            </ul>
            <p>Employers hire candidates who demonstrate capability. BridgeDegree helps you prove that capability before graduation.</p>
          </div>
        </details>
        <details class="faq-item">
          <summary>How does BridgeDegree support students who want to study abroad?</summary>
          <div class="faq-answer">
            <p>BridgeDegree prepares students for global opportunities years before application season. Support includes:</p>
            <ul>
              <li>Scholarship strategy planning</li>
              <li>Research publication support</li>
              <li>Visa coaching</li>
              <li>International CV preparation</li>
              <li>Visa pathway guidance</li>
              <li>Global career positioning</li>
            </ul>
            <p>This ensures students are admission-ready and scholarship-ready when the time comes.</p>
          </div>
        </details>
        <details class="faq-item">
          <summary>Can BridgeDegree help me work remotely for international companies?</summary>
          <div class="faq-answer">
            <p>Yes. BridgeDegree prepares students for the global remote workforce by training them in:</p>
            <ul>
              <li>Remote collaboration tools</li>
              <li>International workplace standards</li>
              <li>Asynchronous communication</li>
              <li>Cross-cultural teamwork</li>
            </ul>
            <p>Students may also participate in remote international projects that build credibility with global employers.</p>
          </div>
        </details>
        <details class="faq-item">
          <summary>What does 'career infrastructure' mean?</summary>
          <div class="faq-answer">
            <p>A coaching service gives you advice and skills. BridgeDegree gives you verifiable credentials. After BridgeDegree, you hold a blockchain-authenticated Career Passport containing 2+ years of documented work experience, at least one indexed publication, and a globally legible professional profile.</p>
          </div>
        </details>
        <details class="faq-item">
          <summary>Can I join if I am in 400 or 500 Level?</summary>
          <div class="faq-answer">
            <p>Yes. Final-year students can join and still benefit from the Publication Pipeline, Career Passport build, and employer placement support.</p>
          </div>
        </details>
        <details class="faq-item">
          <summary>Is BridgeDegree affiliated with any Nigerian university?</summary>
          <div class="faq-answer">
            <p>No. BridgeDegree operates independently of any university. We do not require institutional approval or affiliation. Individual lecturers and departmental staff at many universities recommend BridgeDegree to their students — but the platform is not a university product.</p>
          </div>
        </details>
        <details class="faq-item">
          <summary>What is the Publication Pipeline?</summary>
          <div class="faq-answer">
            <p>The Publication Pipeline supports the submission of your final-year project to an approved, indexed, peer-reviewed journal. Your existing final-year work is aligned to an industry brief, co-authored with a supervisor or expert, and prepared for submission. Also, you can co-author publications before your final year.</p>
          </div>
        </details>
        <details class="faq-item">
          <summary>What is the Global Mobility Framework?</summary>
          <div class="faq-answer">
            <p>The Global Mobility Framework is a premium add-on. It includes scholarship strategy, SOP development, international CV, ATS calibration, study abroad support, LinkedIn optimisation, NYSC integration, and post-graduation migration support.</p>
          </div>
        </details>
        <details class="faq-item">
          <summary>What does 'blockchain-credentialed' mean?</summary>
          <div class="faq-answer">
            <p>Your credentials are recorded on a tamper-proof, decentralised digital ledger. Any employer can visit BridgeDegree's verification portal, enter your Passport reference, and instantly confirm the authenticity of your credentials. The record cannot be altered or faked.</p>
          </div>
        </details>
        <details class="faq-item">
          <summary>Does BridgeDegree guarantee internships?</summary>
          <div class="faq-answer">
            <p>BridgeDegree connects students with structured internship opportunities and industry projects through corporate partners. While placements depend on student readiness and performance, the platform is designed to increase access to real professional experience during university.</p>
          </div>
        </details>
        <details class="faq-item">
          <summary>Does BridgeDegree guarantee jobs?</summary>
          <div class="faq-answer">
            <p>BridgeDegree does not promise jobs. Instead, it builds the career capital employers look for, including experience, skills, and documented achievements. Students who complete the programme are significantly more competitive in the job market.</p>
          </div>
        </details>
